 <H1>Cursors</H1> 
 <P><UL>
<LI><H2>Can declare a cursor on a relation or query statement (which generates a relation).
</H2>
</UL><UL>
<LI><H2>Can open a cursor, and repeatedly fetch a tuple then move the cursor, until all tuples have been retrieved.
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>Can use a special clause, called ORDER BY, in queries that are accessed through a cursor, to control the order in which tuples are returned.
<UL>
<LI>Fields in ORDER BY clause must also appear in SELECT clause.
</UL><LI>The ORDER BY clause, which orders answer tuples, is only allowed in the context of a cursor.
</UL></UL><UL>
<LI><H2>Can also modify/delete tuple pointed to by a cursor.</H2>
</UL></P>
